@startuml
title Viaverse Chat Message Delivery — Sequence Diagram

actor "Sender Client" as A
participant "API Gateway / Realtime BFF" as BFF
participant "chat-service" as Chat
participant "marketplace-service" as Marketplace
participant "safety-service" as Safety
database "Cassandra / Message Store" as DB
participant "notification-service" as Notification
actor "Recipient Client" as B

A -> BFF : send message / websocket or HTTPS
BFF -> Chat : SendMessage(command)
Chat -> Marketplace : validate job participants/state
Chat -> Safety : scan text/media refs
Safety --> Chat : allow / warn / hold / block
Chat -> DB : persist message + receipt state
Chat -> Notification : notify if offline
Chat --> BFF : delivery event
BFF --> B : realtime delivery
B -> BFF : read receipt
BFF -> Chat : UpdateReceipt

note bottom
Realtime transport is adapter-level.
Core chat-service should work with WebSocket, SSE or polling.
Message persistence and safety policy stay independent from transport.
end note
@enduml
